      "section": [
        "Waterbender prison",
        "History"
      ],
      "text": "Hama, the last waterbender of the Southern Water Tribe to be taken away by the Fire Nation, was brought here upon her capture. After staying here for most of her life, she discovered that during the full moon, her waterbending abilities improved dramatically and she was able to control the water inside other bodies, thus discovering the art of bloodbending."
    },
    {
      "body": "After practicing the newly discovered art on the ${link_0} in her cage, she successfully performed the technique on one of the guards and manipulated him into unlocking her cage. Hama promptly walked out of the prison as a free woman for the first time in years.",
      "links": [
